(5, 'CUP holds 1st Organizational Fair', 'Nicole B. Soer', 'cup-holds-1st-organizational-fair', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The City University of Pasay begins another breakthrough as they officially held their very first Organization Fair on July 14-15, 2016 which was done at the school grounds.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;With their hardworking effort and passion to make a change, the different organizations within the university cooperatively made this event possible. All with one goal: to discover and give each student a chance to be part of what they love most. </p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On the first day, July 14, 2016, at exactly 9:00 in the morning the event began. The opening message was given by the Associate VPAA Dr. Rosanie F. Estuche followed by the CUP President Dr. Concepcion C. Libuit for her inspirational message. After the special messages, the induction of officers for every college and every organization was held, followed by the ribbon cutting, then the official opening of each booth presented by the different organizations. For the rest of the day and the following days (July 15, 2016), all the students of the university were allowed to look into the booths and join different organizations they were interested in. </p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thus, this concludes the very first organization fair for the City University of Pasay. What a pleasure it is to witness something new to be written down in the history of the university.</p>'),
(6, 'Buwan ng Wika 2016 Celebrated', 'Nicole B. Soer', 'buwan-ng-wika-2016-celebrated', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The City University of Pasay celebrated one of the most anticipated events among the students, <span style="font-style: italic;">Buwan ng Wika</span> or National Language Month from August 24-26 at the university ground floor with the theme, <span style="font-style: italic;">Filipino: Wika ng Karunungan.</span></p><p><span style="font-style: italic;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>A mass was held on the first day of the said event. It was then followed by the speeches from our beloved professors, Professor Eligia T. Lopena the Filipino Adviser and Dr. Ana Marie V. Barbieto, the College of Education, Dean. After that, the Filipino major students performed a remarkable play of the most significant part of Ibong Adarna, Florante at Laura, El Filibusterismo and Noli Me Tangere. The second day was quite more exciting because of the different competitions like Pagsulat ng Sanaysay, Masining Pagkukwento and Sayawit. The speakers for that day were Dr. Concepcion C. Libuit -CUP President, Dr. Rosanie F. Estuche - Associate VP for Academics and Professor Erlinda R. Miranda - Filipino Professor. The search for Malakas and Maganda was the last event that occurred on the third day. </p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Winners in the respective competitions were announced at the latter part of the program.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>'),
(7, 'English Circle showcase Spoken Word Poetry', 'Nicole B. Soer', 'english-circle-showcase-spoken-word-poetry', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;With the theme, English: The Language of the Global Society, the English Circle initiated the celebration of the English Week as they brought a new avenue of performing arts-the Spoken Word Poetry on December 9, 2016 at the CUP Library.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Different students from the College of Education showcased their talents in this art as they performed their very own piece. Before the said program, the committee requested some professors to choose literary pieces that they will read to the students. These professors gladly agreed and happily read their chosen pieces before the audience. They were Dr. Lurida Ramos, Dr. Rosalinda Llamas, Dr. Remedios Bal''Oro, Prof. Melvin Crisostomo, Prof. Eroll Beja and Prof. Emmanuel Luna who showed their love and passion for this art presentation. </p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Spoken Word Society is one of the highlights of the celebration which is a contemporary way of expressive poetry performed in different places like faces, restaurants and even in some schools. Nowadays, this new trend inspires teenagers especially college students around Metro Manila to write poems and to express themselves through this stage arts.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Overall, the event was done successfully with the efforts of the BSE IV-1 major in English. Dr. Rosalinda Llamas gave her closing remarks as she motivates each of the students specifically those budding writers to never give up their dreams and continue their passion in writing.</p>'),
(8, 'OSA conducts Leadership Training Seminar', 'Nicole B. Soer', 'osa-conducts-leadership-training-seminar', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Office of the Student Affairs conducted the annual leadership training for college student councils and officers of recognized campus organizations last August 16, 2016 at the Function Hall of Cuneta Astrodome.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The seminar was organized by the Dean of the Office of Student Affairs, Prof. Melvin M. Crisostomo who poured out all his hard work and time to make the said event successful.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The seminar began with a prayer from the CSC President, Ms. Reysie Ann Poblador. As the programme continued, the first resource speaker, Dr. Estrellita Puti-an gave a very important message regarding Roles, Responsibilities and Practices in Handling Student Governance. Later on that day, the second resource speaker Prof. Eroll A. Beja discussed about the value of Leadership Strategies as student leaders. During the second half of the day, the next resource speaker, Dr. Maribel R. Gabuat discussed her lesson regarding Dynamic leadership, Communication and Influencing Style. It was then followed by the last resource speaker Prof. Marcos B. Geronga with his topic Solution Focused Coaching for Leaders.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As the day came to an end, the closing remarks was given by VPAd, Martin Elwood S. Rivera. The different student leaders went home with plenty of knowledge in stock for their leadership roles.</p>'),
